1 (f) The levels of the career ladder are as follows:
2 (1) Level one is a State certified teacher;
3 (2) Level two is a teacher pursuing:
4 (i) A master’s degree;
5 (ii) 30 credits of a program of study approved by the State Board, in
6 consultation with the Professional Standards and Teacher Education Board; or
7 (iii) NBC;
8 (3) Level three is:
9 (i) An NBC teacher;
10 (ii) If there is no assessment comparable to NBC for the teacher’s
11 subject area, a teacher with a master’s degree in the teacher’s subject area; or
12 (iii) An assistant principal; and
13 (4) Level four is:
14 (i) A teacher on the teacher leadership track, in the following tiers:
15 1. Lead Teacher;
16 2. Distinguished Teacher; or
17 3. Professor Distinguished Teacher; or
18 (ii) A teacher on the administrator track, in the following tiers:
19 1. Licensed Principal; or
20 2. Distinguished Principal.
21 6–1003.
22 (a) Beginning with teachers listed under § 6–1002(h)(3) of this subtitle, as
23 specified by the State Board, a teacher on level one, two, or three of the career ladder shall:
24 (1) Teach in the classroom on average [60%] 80% of the teacher’s working
25 time; and
26 (2) Spend the remaining time on other teacher activities, including:

