1 (i) Improving instruction;
2 (ii) Identifying, working with, and tutoring students who need
3 additional help;
4 (iii) Working with the most challenging students;
5 (iv) Working with students living in concentrated poverty; and
6 (v) Leading or participating in professional learning.
7 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
8 1, 2025.

